  "notes": [
    "High-level design: The application consists of stateless APIs and stateful databases. AWS Load Balancer Controller will provision an Internet-facing ALB in public subnets, routing traffic to the internal 'api-gateway' service on port 9090. HTTP-only is sufficient for baseline validation.",
    "Node sizing math: 8 total pods. Assigned default 512 Mi each (user=512Mi, project=512Mi, task=512Mi, api=512Mi, api-gateway=512Mi, postgresql=512Mi, mysql=512Mi, mongo=512Mi). Total pod memory requests = 4096 Mi (~4.0 GiB). A t3.small node provides 1.4 GiB allocatable. 4.0 GiB / 1.4 GiB = ~2.85 nodes. Provisioning 4 nodes to provide sufficient capacity and margin for system DaemonSets.",
    "Add-ons required: Core EKS add-ons (vpc-cni, kube-proxy, coredns) are mandatory, with vpc-cni deployed before node groups (before_compute = true). Since PVCs are required, the AWS EBS CSI driver must be installed and configured with a default StorageClass.",
    "Discrepancy - Workload Types: Kompose generated naked Pods because the Compose file used 'restart: no' and 'restart: on-failure'. For a robust Kubernetes deployment, the stateless services (user, project, task, api, api-gateway) must be deployed as Deployments, and the stateful databases (postgresql, mysql, mongo) must be deployed as StatefulSets.",
    "Stateful constraints: 'postgresql' uses /var/lib/postgresql/data; 'mysql' uses /var/lib/mysql; 'mongo' uses /data/db and /data/configdb. All require PVCs provided via the EBS CSI driver. Since the databases are single-replica setups for this baseline, ReadWriteOnce PVCs are appropriate.",
    "Kompose warning check: 'File don't exist... stat' warnings appeared because Kompose attempted to evaluate local directory structures for volume mounts. We correctly ignore local bindings and use PVCs for the runtime database paths.",
    "Missing dependencies: Kubernetes lacks Docker Compose's 'depends_on' functionality. App containers may crash and restart during initial boot while databases initialize. This will be naturally mitigated by standard Kubernetes CrashLoopBackOff and restart policies in Deployments/StatefulSets."
